The paper deals with sequence prediction, which is a problem commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The use of probabilistic measures such as total variation and Kullback-Leibler divergence also suggests a connection to information theory. The paper also discusses the concept of stochastic processes, which is a topic in both data science (cs.DS) and systems and control (cs.SI).
